This paper deals with the problem of maximizing social welfare in cognitive radio networks, which is a topic related to network optimization and game theory. The paper also considers spectrum uncertainty and sensing inaccuracy, which are issues related to information theory and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). However, the paper also involves optimization and game theory, which are topics covered by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes algorithms and models for decision-making, which are topics covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
